HEADWORD: Progenerate
<hw>Pro*gen"er*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>progeneratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>progenerare</ets> to beget;
<ets>pro</ets> forth, forward + <ets>generare</ets> to generate.]</ety>
<def>To beget; to generate; to produce; to procreate; <as>as, to
<ex>progenerate</ex> a race</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Landor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Progeneration</ent>⟦br⟧
